      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long does it take to see improvements in brain fog with Reviv?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>It is impossible to say for sure.</p><p>But i have seen a number of folks begin to notice improvements within 2-3 months of consistent use. </p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_tUj3HX": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will I experience headaches when using Reviv for brain fog?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>In my personal experience this was the case and I viewed the headache to sort of be a symbol of progress as I often felt a bit clearer after such headaches.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_6bErhk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can Reviv help with brain fog if I've tried everything else?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I cannot promise you anything.  All i can say is that it has helped a number of people with brain fog already (including myself).</p><p>And it is a pretty inexpensive, uninvasive thing to try.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_jEbzGk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Do I need to make other lifestyle changes while using Reviv for brain fog?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I do not really view that you do.</p><p>But you should 'listen' to your body.  For me this means that i eat when i am hungry and I sleep when I am tired.</p><p>Pretty simple.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
